channel.title: Help.. Experienced coders only please. EOF Tag
channel.description:
Hello, I am currently working on something very advanced for my server and I found out I would need some things, that I have no idea about. Help if you can.
EOF Tag -> What is an EOF Tag? [Example] What does an EOF Tag do? [Main Purpose] Why is an EOF tag important? [Able to move on without it]
All Help is appreaciated =]!

item.title: Help.. Experienced coders only please. EOF Tag
item.dc:creator: @bl4ck_ra1nb0w bl4ck ra1nb0w
item.description:
@bl4ck_ra1nb0w wrote:

[quote=“I Am Olan14, post:4, topic:109750”]End Of File, they should be in your .cfg’s, in your java files it uses BufferedReader to read the files and theres a part where it says if it finds [EOF] in the file that tells it to stop reading.
Don’t know how to put it any cleared then that.[/quote]

Thanks a lot… Thought as much… Working on my screencut.cfg . Pretty close to making cutscenes. Zerofreeze’s work helped me a lot.
